AB  - This paper demonstrates the importance of allowing for structural breaks in the time-series when investigating the relationship between the official and the parallel markets in foreign exchange. Only when structural breaks are accounted for does a relationship emerge in Nigeria. We find that over the period 1980–1993, the official rate has Granger-caused the parallel rate.
